<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-078-918  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 078 918.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  Nov 1989 v38 n11 p1481(12).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Local concurrent error detection and correction in data structuresusing virtual backpointers. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Li, Chung-Chi Jim; Chen, Paul Peichuan; Fuchs, W. Kent.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Algorithms for error detection and correction of linked datastructures should not access a large number of nodes off theintended traversal path to limit performance degradation.andP;  A newtechnique for detecting and correcting linked data structureerrors called the virtual backpointer is presented that generatesbackpointer values used in backward traversals in addition toproviding structural error detection and correction.andP;  The VirtualDouble-Linked List (VDLL) and B-Tree with Virtual Backpointers arethe two data structures developed using the virtual backpointer:the former requires the same amount of storage as the standarddouble-linked list but has higher error detection and correctioncapabilities, and the latter requires that 'm' + 4 fields be addedto each standard B-tree node for backward traversals and errordetection and correction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Concurrency ControlAlgorithm AnalysisNew TechniqueTheoretical ResearchError-Correcting CodesData StructuresError CheckingRobustnessFault Tolerance.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   Checking windows for a double-linked list. (chart)Virtual double-linked list (VDLL) of five nodes. (chart)Detectability D-s of several linked list data structures. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>